🔹 1. Members Overview
GET /api/businesses/:id/rbac-summary/
Expect:
total_members
total_roles
total_permissions
recent_members (optional)
🔹 2. Members List
GET /api/businesses/:id/members/
Expect:
member_id (UUID)
user info (email/username)
roles (array)
joined_at
🔹 3. Roles
GET /api/businesses/:id/roles/

POST /api/businesses/:id/roles/

{ "name": "Manager" }
PATCH /api/businesses/:id/roles/:role_id/
DELETE /api/businesses/:id/roles/:role_id/
🔹 4. Role Permissions
GET /api/businesses/:id/permissions/ → catalog
GET /api/businesses/:id/roles/:role_id/permissions/

POST /api/businesses/:id/roles/:role_id/permissions/

{ "permission_id": 3 }
DELETE /api/businesses/:id/roles/:role_id/permissions/:permission_id/
🔹 5. Member Role Assignment

POST /api/businesses/:id/members/:member_id/roles/

{ "role_id": 2 }
DELETE /api/businesses/:id/members/:member_id/roles/:role_id/
🔹 6. Access Check (CRITICAL)
GET /api/businesses/:id/access/
Expect:
roles: []
permissions: []

👉 This is what your frontend must trust.

🔹 7. Permission Enforcement

Test manually:

user without roles.view → cannot open roles page
user without roles.manage → cannot:
create role
assign permission
delete role
🔹 8. Edge Cases (don’t skip)
Assign same role twice → should NOT duplicate
Assign same permission twice → should NOT duplicate
Delete role in use → should fail or handle cleanly
Remove last owner → must be blocked
🔹 9. UI Flow Checks
Switch role → permissions reload instantly
Assign permission → appears without refresh
Remove → disappears instantly
Sidebar navigation → all members routes work